I stay at a hotel near there quite often for business. On 2 separate occasions Ive tried to eat there and wasnt able to.  The 1st time I attempted to call and place my order over the phone so that I could walk over and pick it up when ready. The rudest person ever answered the phone and as soon as I asked to place a to-go order, they promptly hung up the phone on me. I said ok, maybe it was an accident so I called back and again, the person picked up the phone and slammed it back down on me. A 3rd time I called and when the person answered I said " Yes, hello....Ive called twice already to place an order and someone has hung up on me both times" The person said in a very hostile manner, "Obviously that means we dont take phone orders" and hung up on me for a 3rd time. I ended up ordering from a local pizza place. I mean how rude can you be!  On a different day I said ok, I'll jus walk over and order to go. The line was out the door and it was freezing this night.  Everyone in line was waiting to dine-in so I attempted to go in to place my order to go. A big man with his back to the glass door stopped me and told me to wait in line and wouldnt even open the door. I said "sir I just want to order to go, not dine in". He said nothing further, would not let me open the door to come in and just pointed to the back of the line. It is utterly ridiculous that I should have to wait in a long line of people waiting to dine in just to place a to go order. So again, I left disappointed for a 2nd time. At this point, I have never tasted their food, and I never will. I do not choose to spend my $$ at places that display such horrible hospitality. And you should not waste your time or money either.

I didnt learn my lesson there and went to their silver spring location once with one of my friends. The server was a mid aged heavyset gentleman with glasses. He wasnt rude but I assume he was either forgetful or very overwhelmed as it was late at night. He greeted us a few minutes after we sat down and we asked for waters and told him we will be ready to order in one minute. I kid you not, he came back over 15 minutes later. We ordered, and the food took about 7 eternities to come out, at which point we had started eating some jam because we were so hungry. You know when you’re so hungry anything tastes good? Well not this time. I believe i had fish and chips or something like that and the breading on the fish was soggy and it was falling off.
